Step-by-Step Instructions: Health Guardian Setup
1. Install Prerequisites
Make sure you have the following installed:

Node.js (version 14.x or higher)
npm (Node Package Manager)
Verify installation by running:

bash
Copy code
node -v
npm -v

2. Clone the Repository
Clone the project and navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/health-guardian.git
cd health-guardian
3. Install Dependencies
Install the required dependencies:

bash
Copy code
npm install
This will install the following:

express: Web framework
bcryptjs: Password hashing
jsonwebtoken: Authentication
multer: File uploads

4. Project Structure
Ensure the project has the following structure:

bash
Copy code
/my_project
    /uploads         # Stores uploaded prescriptions
    /public          # HTML, CSS, and static assets
    server.js        # Node.js server file
    package.json     # Project configuration
5. Run the Server
Start the Node.js server:

bash
Copy code
node server.js
You should see Server running on port 3000 in the terminal.

6. Access the Application
Open your browser and navigate to the following pages:

Home Page: http://localhost:3000
Login Page: http://localhost:3000/login.html
Signup Page: http://localhost:3000/signup.html
Dashboard: http://localhost:3000/dashboard.html (only accessible after login)
7. User Registration and Login
Sign Up: Go to /signup.html to create a new account.
Login: Use your credentials at /login.html to log in.
Access Dashboard: After logging in, you'll be redirected to the dashboard.
8. Upload Prescriptions
In the dashboard (/dashboard.html):

Select a file using the Choose File button.
Click Upload to upload the file. Uploaded files are saved in the /uploads folder.